OL,3,CCalls to revisit assisted dying debate
OL,4,Cin Guernsey
OL,6,FDeputy Carl Meerveld voted against the
OL,7,F2018 assisted dying proposition but
OL,8,Fwould like to see the topic debated
OL,9,Fagain.
OL,11,FHe explains: "I've said publically as
OL,12,Fan individual if I were facing that
OL,13,Fterrible situation, I would want to
OL,14,Fhave the choice.
OL,16,F"But as a representative of the
OL,17,Fpeople, we have to then think about
OL,18,Fthe unintended consequences of
OL,19,Fimplementing that, the cost and
OL,20,Fdifficulty of implementing it, and how
OL,21,Fyou maintain it."
